## Vercel Web Analytics Installation Complete

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

### Changes Made

**1. Package Installation**
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (version 1.4.1)
- Used npm to ensure consistency with existing package manager

**2. Modified Files**
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics component to root layout
  - Imported `Analytics` from `@vercel/analytics/next`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the body section (after ConditionalFooter)
  
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package and its dependencies

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Analytics documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I implemented the Next.js App Router integration pattern:

1. **Framework Detection**: Identified this as a Next.js 16.2.2 project using App Router
2. **Installation**: Used npm (the project's package manager) to install @vercel/analytics
3. **Integration**: Added the Analytics component to the root layout file (`app/layout.tsx`) as per the Next.js App Router instructions
4. **Placement**: Positioned the component at the end of the body section for optimal loading

### Verification Steps Completed

✓ Build successful - Next.js compiled without errors
✓ TypeScript compilation passed
✓ Static page generation completed successfully (12/12 pages)
✓ No new linting errors introduced
✓ All dependencies properly resolved

### Next Steps for Deployment

1. Deploy to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable analytics in the Vercel dashboard:
   - Navigate to Analytics section
   - Select this project
   - Click the Enable button
3. Verify implementation by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view` after deployment

### Technical Notes

- The Analytics component is placed at the end of the body to avoid blocking initial page render
- The component automatically handles development vs. production environments
- No additional configuration is required - analytics will activate once enabled in the Vercel dashboard
- The implementation follows the official Next.js App Router pattern for optimal performance
